ting in Dreadlands (not on role, not on anon, it was visible they were there) and I am the one he asked for a rez.  You tell me what THAT says about their guild.<br><br>Ullric in general was a jack ass as well.  The few times I grouped with him he would pull stupid stunts like going into sebilis crypt and then five minutes later he wanted to leave to join a guild group.  While my guild was in Ssra Temple last week Ullric was there and kept saying stuff like &quot;/tell Faranor Yeah once they get to the first safe spot I'll train them&quot;.  Yes I know he was joking, but you don't joke about that stuff when you're guild has a bad rep anyway, especially when you are an OFFICER.<br><br>Now THAT'S just some examples of actions by OFFICERS in the guild.  If that's not enough, I'll cite a few more examples from members leaving out names this time.<br><br>Frenzy group in Lower Guk many many moons ago.  Two Tides of Valor members in the group, one (a warrior) has FBSS, his friend (a paladin) doesn't have one and wants one bad.  I am all for need before greed, but this was back when FBSS was about 10k and there was no convincing other people in the group about that idea heh.  Anyway, the paladin ends up leaving about 10 minutes before FBSS drops.  We roll and I win, until the warrior decides to roll for his friend and he tops my number.  Now the leader of the group was in a weird situation.  He couldn't give it to the warrior because it's lore, he couldn't give it to the paladin cause he had left the group.  He gives me the FBSS and says I earned it, I do whatever I want with it.  The ToV guy starts sending me tells that I should let his friend have it since he beat my roll.  I think to myself &quot;this is fair, I won't use this only sell it anyway&quot;.  I agree and he says we will meet his friend in EC.  Unfortunately bad timing steps in the way and I need to log briefly for about 30 minutes.  The warrior asks me to give it to this third party person to transfer to his friend.  So I agree (yes this was a mistake not handing it to his friend directly, my trust for Tides members was high at this point though <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :( --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/frown.gif ALT=":("><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> )  When I log back on thirty minutes later in EC, the warrior is auctioning the FBSS for sale for 10k.  I send him a tell asking him what's going on and he says &quot;Just selling the FBSS, my friend didn't want it&quot;.  At this point I am so mad at myself and him I don't know what to do.  I contact the third party person holding the sash and ask him what's up.  He says something weird is going on and he thinks the guy is going to &quot;purchase&quot; the FBSS with an alt.  At this point the third party person screws over the warrior and sells the FBSS and gives me 3k for my &quot;troubles&quot;  /sigh<br><br>I have more examples I have posted in the past (such as Zerbrista's actions, etc, etc) but I see no need to continue with pages and pages.  I won't tell you how many Tides members used to sign on and send me messages filled with insults and nasty language just because I had posted some truth about them on this board (/shrug that's a decent guild right?).  As it's been said before, when there are so many a-holes in one guild, it's hard to find the good apples in the bunch (although I do know many exist). <p><a target="Shortyrez Starfury" href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=45788">Shortyrez Starfury</a><BR>60th High Priest of Brell <BR>Final Destiny, Ayonae Ro</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#383838><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub42.ezboard.com/umokasstardust.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Mokas Stardust</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Board Veteran</span><br> <font color=#ff0000>(2/3/02 10:56:47 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub42.ezboard.com/fayonaerofrm6.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=880.